He was denied his own identity.
That's when February 11, 2015, Auer walked out of the meeting and kicked a transpol waiting lounge on television.
Later, a work of art called Monument for the Excluded was born on television, in which Auer reflects his experience of power and its use.
"It's crazy that any person who is defined as a woman at birth can magnifying their breasts, but you need a diagnosis to remove your breasts," Auer tells me.
Your body is not yours if you feel that you are different than the amount of your gender determined at birth.
