Trump's actions drew attention in February as Air Force One rolled into the background of a presidential campaign event in Melbourne, Florida. Trump has strongly criticized his predecessor's presidential plane use on Twitter.
"The White House is very pleased with the Made in America event, which introduced products made from American materials by American workers from all 50 states," said White House Press Secretary Lindsay Walters.
The crews of the HMX-1 unit regularly conduct training flights in the Washington area and practice on a southern grassy field bringing the president to the White House intent accuracy.
